To see this truly makes me sad.

"I saw an army. A sea of black and gold."
Such a great way to describe Nilfgaard (from the Northern perspective) in two short sentences. Nilfgaard is by far the biggest and most advanced economy in the Witcher world and has a massive army. For example, the Empire deployed over 300 thousands soldiers during the Second Northern War (will take place in the show).

snippet.textDisplay: This could go either way, and it's hilarious that that baddest army in the Continent still got stuck with that goofy looking nut sack armor! Anya Chalotra is pretty as a picture, but she looks and sounds too young to convincingly pull off Yennefer, for me. She lacks the effortless confidence that characterizes Yennefer in the books and the games alike. I suspect that Henry will be the best thing about this series, here. I guess I should give it a shot before I say much more, of course, and I likely will.
